      "error_message": "expo prebuild crash: Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'extract')",
      "file": "apps/mobile/package.json",
      "root_cause": "tar override pinned to ^7.5.15. tar v7 exports __esModule:true with default:undefined. Expo CLI's _interopRequireDefault(require('tar')) sees __esModule:true and returns the module as-is, so _tar().default is undefined. Calling .extract() on undefined crashes. tar v6 is CommonJS (no __esModule), so interop wraps it as {default: tar} and _tar().default.extract() works.",
